    "tooltips": {
      "m": "Cont r a = (a ⟶ r) ⟶ r — m is waiting for its continuation. It does not run yet.",
      "f": "(a ⟶ Cont r b) — the continuation step; given a, produces a Cont r b action",
      "k": "(b ⟶ r) — the downstream continuation: what happens after b is produced",
      "compose": "Build inner continuation k2 = \\\\a -> f(a)(k)\\nThis closure captures both f and k.\\nWhen called with a, it: runs f(a) to get Cont r b, then runs that with k.",
      "k2": "(a ⟶ r) — the composed continuation. When m eventually produces a, it calls k2(a), which runs f(a) and then k.",
      "run": "Run m with k2: m(k2). m runs LAST — this is the inversion of control.\\nIf callCC is used, k (the downstream continuation) can be captured as an escape function.",
      "r": "r — the final result of the entire composed computation"
    },
    "title": "Cont bind: build inner continuation k2 = (a → f(a)(k)), give k2 to m — also called: >>=",
    "name": "bind"
  }
